data.description: Welcome to this exquisite 4-bedroom, 2.5-bath home nestled in the charming town of Gainesville, Georgia, just a few miles away from the renowned Chateau Elan and the vibrant downtown Braselton. This meticulously maintained residence boasts a host of upgrades, including a modernized kitchen adorned with stainless steel appliances and a convenient island with power outlets, perfect for culinary enthusiasts. The main level showcases newly installed bamboo hardwood floors that exude warmth and elegance, a master on main with big windows showcasing the garden, as well as a tastefully remodeled fireplace enveloped in custom stone. In addition, you will find a cozy office area with newly installed French doors. Step outside to discover a backyard oasis, complete with new retaining walls, a custom-covered pergola, an extended patio, and a lush garden area. The generous backyard extension features Zoysia grass, offering a serene retreat. Inside, the house has been freshly painted, and new faux wood blinds adorn the windows. Ascend the newly modernized staircase to find 3 bedrooms on the second floor, as well as a full bath. The property also boasts practical upgrades, such as a new AC unit, water heater, and roof. With two attics for ample storage, this Gainesville gem offers both style and functionality for comfortable living.
